===全球导航卫星系统===

美国[[空军太空司令部|空军太空司令部]]运营的[[全球定位系统|全球定位系统]]（GPS）提供了非常准确的定时和频率信号。GPS接收器通过测量至少四个但通常更多的GPS卫星的信号的相对时间延迟来工作，每个GPS卫星至少具有两个机载[[铯|铯]]和两个[[铷|铷]][[原子钟|原子钟]]。相对时间在数学上转换为三个绝对空间坐标和一个绝对时间坐标。<ref name="gps.gov">{{cite web |url=http://www.gps.gov/systems/gps |title=Global Positioning System |publisher=Gps.gov |accessdate=2010-06-26 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100730173245/http://www.gps.gov/systems/gps |archivedate=2010-07-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref> GPS时间（GPST）是一个连续的时间标度，理论上精确到大约14[[纳秒|纳秒]]。<ref>{{cite journal |author=David W. Allan |url=http://www.allanstime.com/Publications/DWA/Science_Timekeeping/TheScienceOfTimekeeping.pdf |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025234726/http://www.allanstime.com/Publications/DWA/Science_Timekeeping/TheScienceOfTimekeeping.pdf |title=The Science of Timekeeping |publisher=Hewlett Packard |year=1997 |archivedate=2012-10-25 |access-date=2020-10-25 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 然而，大多数接收器在信号中会失去准确性，并且仅精确到100[[纳秒|纳秒]]。<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.pdana.com/PHDWWW_files/gpsrole.pdf|title=The Role of GPS in Precise Time and Frequency Dissemination|publisher=GPSworld|date=July–August 1990|accessdate=2014-04-27|journal=|archive-date=2012-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121215031941/http://www.pdana.com/PHDWWW_files/gpsrole.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atomic-clock.galleon.eu.com/support/gps-time-accuracy.html|title=GPS time accurate to 100 nanoseconds|publisher=Galleon|accessdate=2012-10-12|archive-date=2012-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120514001920/http://www.atomic-clock.galleon.eu.com/support/gps-time-accuracy.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> GPST与TAI（国际原子时间）和UTC（协调世界时）相关，但有所不同。GPST与TAI保持恒定的偏移量（TAI–GPST=19秒），并且像TAI一样不执行[[闰秒|闰秒]]。定期对卫星中的车载时钟进行校正，以使其与地面时钟保持同步。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://confluence.qps.nl/display/KBE/UTC+to+GPS+Time+Correction|title=UTC to GPS Time Correction|website=qps.nl|access-date=2020-10-25|archive-date=2017-03-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170321094832/https://confluence.qps.nl/display/KBE/UTC+to+GPS+Time+Correction|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=NAVSTAR GPS User Equipment Introduction|url=http://www.navcen.uscg.gov/pubs/gps/gpsuser/gpsuser.pdf|accessdate=2020-10-25|archive-date=2013-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131021060507/http://www.navcen.uscg.gov/pubs/gps/gpsuser/gpsuser.pdf|dead-url=no}} Section 1.2.2</ref>  GPS导航消息包括GPST和UTC之间的差异。截至2015年7月，GPST比UTC提前17秒，因为UTC在2015年6月30日增加了[[闰秒|闰秒]]。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.navcen.uscg.gov/?pageName=currentNanus&format=txt |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2020-10-25 |archive-date=2017-05-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521000000/http://www.navcen.uscg.gov/?pageName=currentNanus&format=txt |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://gps.afspc.af.mil/gps/archive/2012/nanus/2012034.nnu |title=Notice Advisory to Navstar Users (NANU) 2012034 |date=2012-05-30 |accessdate=2012-07-02 |publisher=GPS Operations Center |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130408111458/https://gps.afspc.af.mil/gps/archive/2012/nanus/2012034.nnu |archivedate=2013-04-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref>接收机从GPS时间中减去此偏移量以计算UTC和特定时区值。

[[俄罗斯航天集团|俄罗斯航天集团]]运营的[[格洛纳斯系统|格洛纳斯系统]]（GLONASS）提供了全球定位系统（GPS）系统的替代方案，并且是第二个在全球范围内运行且具有相当精度的导航系统。GLONASS时间（GLONASST）由GLONASS中央同步器生成，通常优于1000纳秒。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.navipedia.net/index.php/Time_References_in_GNSS|title=Time References in GNSS|website=navipedia.net|access-date=2020-10-25|archive-date=2018-06-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180602120535/http://www.navipedia.net/index.php/Time_References_in_GNSS|dead-url=no}}</ref>与GPS不同，GLONASS时标像UTC一样实现闰秒精确。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.spacecorp.ru/upload/iblock/1c4/cgs-aaixymyt%205.1%20ENG%20v%202014.02.18w.pdf |title=GLONASS Interface Control Document, Navigation radiosignal In bands L1, L2 (ICD L1, L2 GLONASS), Russian Institute of Space Device Engineering, Edition 5.1, 2008 |access-date=2020-10-25 |archive-date=2016-04-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160414062343/http://www.spacecorp.ru/upload/iblock/1c4/cgs-aaixymyt%205.1%20ENG%20v%202014.02.18w.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>

